# Copy to .env and fill in your hostname(s).
#
# DOMAINS is a space-separated list of hostnames where both workers are
# reachable. The proxy takes /v1/* and /_cm/*; the dashboard takes everything
# else. CF Access (Google IdP) should gate each hostname with Bypass rules
# for /v1/* and /_cm/*.
#
# The FIRST entry is the "primary" — it's baked into the burnage CLI as the
# default --url, and passed to the dashboard worker at runtime as env.DOMAIN
# (used for the proxy-URL snippet on the home page). Every listed domain is
# bound as a route on both workers.
DOMAINS="your-domain.example"
